						               													<description>User Summary&amp;#10;Are You &amp;#229;&amp;#139;&amp;#135;&amp;#232;&amp;#128;&amp;#133;&amp;#239;&amp;#188;&amp;#159; (Are You Yuusha?) is a fast-paced were-wolf card game by the Japanese doujin publisher &amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#182;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#173;&amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#149;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#147;&amp;#229;&amp;#183;&amp;#165;&amp;#230;&amp;#136;&amp;#191; released at the Game Market 2015 Autumn convention in Japan.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In Japanese, &amp;#229;&amp;#139;&amp;#135;&amp;#232;&amp;#128;&amp;#133; means 'Hero' so the game name can be translated as 'Are you a Hero?'.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Within 2 rounds only, the monster players must find and eliminate the Hero player to win, otherwise it's the Hero player win.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There is only 1 Hero player card, and there are 5 monster cards available. Each of them has different abilities.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game plays roughly as the following:&amp;#10;1) Each player draws a character card. The players can only check on this character card and must keep it face down so no other player can see who they are.&amp;#10;2) Give two action cards to each player.&amp;#10;3) Before the start of the game, in order all players but one will close their eyes so one can play their power if possible.&amp;#10;4) Round 1 starts. All players discuss and try to figure out the other player's identity. It is of course okay to lie.&amp;#10;5) When time is up or everyone decided, all players put forward one card face down. &amp;#10;6) The players reveal at once who they are going to play their action card against. You can play a card on yourself.&amp;#10;7) Depending on your character, you may reveal you identity and use your ability.&amp;#10;8) All the players reveal their action card and proceed to resolution of their effects. Any player whose HP reaches 0 is KO and is out for the game. They cannot display their action cards not their character card and cannot take part in the discussion until the game ends.&amp;#10;9) Without replenishing action cards, move proceed to Round 2 by repeating steps  4 to 8.&amp;#10;10) The game ends. If the Hero player is still alive he wins. If he's dead the monster players win.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Publisher Summary&amp;#10;&amp;#227;&amp;#128;&amp;#144;Are you &amp;#229;&amp;#139;&amp;#135;&amp;#232;&amp;#128;&amp;#133;&amp;#239;&amp;#188;&amp;#159;&amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#168;&amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#175;&amp;#227;&amp;#128;&amp;#145;&amp;#10;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#187;&amp;#239;&amp;#188;&amp;#147;&amp;#239;&amp;#189;&amp;#158;&amp;#239;&amp;#188;&amp;#148;&amp;#228;&amp;#186;&amp;#186;&amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#167;&amp;#230;&amp;#137;&amp;#139;&amp;#232;&amp;#187;&amp;#189;&amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#171;&amp;#230;&amp;#165;&amp;#189;&amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#151;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#129;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#139;&amp;#228;&amp;#186;&amp;#186;&amp;#231;&amp;#139;&amp;#188;&amp;#229;&amp;#158;&amp;#139;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#178;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#188;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#160;&amp;#10;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#187;&amp;#233;&amp;#173;&amp;#148;&amp;#231;&amp;#142;&amp;#139;&amp;#229;&amp;#190;&amp;#169;&amp;#230;&amp;#180;&amp;#187;&amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#174;&amp;#239;&amp;#188;&amp;#146;&amp;#230;&amp;#151;&amp;#165;&amp;#229;&amp;#190;&amp;#140;&amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#190;&amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#167;&amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#171;&amp;#229;&amp;#139;&amp;#135;&amp;#232;&amp;#128;&amp;#133;&amp;#229;&amp;#189;&amp;#185;&amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#174;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#151;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#172;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#164;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#164;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#188;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#146;&amp;#230;&amp;#142;&amp;#168;&amp;#231;&amp;#144;&amp;#134;&amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#151;&amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#166;&amp;#230;&amp;#148;&amp;#187;&amp;#230;&amp;#146;&amp;#131;&amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#160;&amp;#239;&amp;#188;&amp